EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Diaz, S.333, and Assembly Member Arroyo, A.7007, “AN  ACT  authorizing  the  city  of New York to reconvey its interest in certain real property acquired  by  in  rem  tax  foreclosure  in  the  borough of Bronx to former owner St. Peter's Lutheran Church, notwithstanding  expiration  of  the two year period within which application may be made to the city to  release  its  interest  in  property  thus acquired;  Block  No.   2285, Lot No. 73 on tax map for the borough of Bronx”.
